06:31.450 --> 06:33.584
but just give him a listen,

06:33.618 --> 06:36.420
then make up your mind.

06:40.425 --> 06:42.660
So, uh, we'll just start
playing one of her songs

06:42.694 --> 06:44.829
and then you just
pick it up, play along.

06:48.800 --> 06:50.434
You know what?
Why don't you just

06:50.469 --> 06:51.469
start a beat?

07:23.568 --> 07:26.604
I cannot believe you listen
to your music that loud.

07:26.638 --> 07:29.540
I would say you're gonna
ruin your ears, but...

07:31.743 --> 07:34.445
So you never play
music in the kitchen?

07:34.479 --> 07:35.846
Uh... no.

07:35.881 --> 07:37.548
Music's for the floor.

07:37.582 --> 07:38.682
Oh, right.

07:38.717 --> 07:41.418
You wouldn't want anyone
to have any fun at work.

07:41.453 --> 07:43.687
Excuse me! Am I not fun?

07:43.722 --> 07:45.389
Maybe now.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.458
But at work you're
totally stressed out.

07:47.492 --> 07:48.726
You say "stressed out."

07:48.760 --> 07:50.661
- I say focused.
- Oh.

07:54.432 --> 07:56.734
I have some gelato.

07:56.768 --> 07:59.403
Do you feel like coming up
for some dessert?

08:00.539 --> 08:03.340
Oh, uh...

08:03.375 --> 08:04.508
I don't know.

08:04.543 --> 08:06.544
Oh, I'm sorry. Too focused?

08:09.548 --> 08:12.283
I've already had bugs tonight.
What's a little gelato?

08:26.131 --> 08:27.865
Wow.

08:27.899 --> 08:30.000
Yeah, that was soul-adjacent.

08:30.035 --> 08:31.669
No, that was amazing.

08:31.703 --> 08:33.636
I mean, tell him.
That was fantastic.

08:34.873 --> 08:35.873
Yeah, I think he gets it.

08:40.745 --> 08:43.380
Uh, he says you're not
so bad yourself.

08:44.649 --> 08:45.616
Thank you.

08:50.322 --> 08:52.256
So, uh, what do you think?

08:52.290 --> 08:53.290
Same time tomorrow?

08:54.392 --> 08:56.060
Oh. No, I can't.
I have to work.

08:56.094 --> 08:57.261
Soup kitchen?
Feeding the hungry?

08:57.295 --> 08:59.330
<i>Clothing the...</i>

08:59.364 --> 09:01.298
- Naked?
- Uh.

09:01.333 --> 09:03.133
No, not exactly.

09:03.168 --> 09:05.102
You know Lucie's frozen yogurt?

09:05.136 --> 09:06.870
Oh, yeah! Cool. I mean, uh,

09:06.905 --> 09:08.839
cool... I-I like that place,

09:08.873 --> 09:10.808
not you can't
rehearse tomorrow.

09:10.842 --> 09:12.109
All right.

09:12.143 --> 09:13.844
Okay.

09:15.647 --> 09:16.780
Well, I want a photo of this.

09:16.815 --> 09:19.583
You know?
Our first official photo

09:19.618 --> 09:20.751
of, um...

09:23.555 --> 09:24.922
we're gonna need a name.

09:24.956 --> 09:27.491
So, I guess we're a band?

09:27.525 --> 09:29.460
Okay, we're a band!

09:29.494 --> 09:30.694
All right!

09:34.399 --> 09:35.666
All right.

09:37.602 --> 09:39.570
Awesome sauce.

09:39.604 --> 09:41.372
Awesome sauce?

09:41.406 --> 09:44.341
Yeah. You know?

09:44.376 --> 09:45.442
All right. Well,

09:45.477 --> 09:47.111
I'll text you later
to figure out a time.

09:47.145 --> 09:49.113
- Cool.
- Okay.

09:49.147 --> 09:50.114
Bye, Emmett.

09:55.153 --> 09:56.120
What?

10:02.060 --> 10:04.828
No. We're not...

10:04.863 --> 10:07.865
she has a boyfriend.

10:09.000 --> 10:10.934
Really.

10:10.969 --> 10:12.836
His name is jed.

10:15.707 --> 10:17.574
What was that?

10:19.544 --> 10:21.645
Right.

10:21.680 --> 10:22.880
It's a good sign.

10:28.453 --> 10:30.621
Goat cheese and fig.

10:30.655 --> 10:33.724
No, thanks. I'm still thinking
about those grasshoppers.

10:37.295 --> 10:38.429
Who's that?

10:38.463 --> 10:41.465
Mm. That's Bruno.

10:41.499 --> 10:43.267
I was basically his
indentured servant

10:43.301 --> 10:44.334
for a year in normandy.

10:44.369 --> 10:47.037
You apprenticed in France?

10:47.072 --> 10:49.173
That's my dream!

10:49.207 --> 10:51.075
Well, I'd be happy to
give you a recommendation.

10:51.109 --> 10:54.178
He was brutal with me,
but I'm sure he'd love you.

10:54.212 --> 10:57.014
Yeah, right.
An American girl who's deaf?

10:57.048 --> 10:59.149
Hey, just because
I was an idiot

10:59.184 --> 11:01.118
doesn't mean everybody will be.

11:02.921 --> 11:04.054
Except your hands

11:04.089 --> 11:06.657
are way too pretty.

11:06.691 --> 11:08.792
What's wrong with my hands?

11:08.827 --> 11:10.894
You work in a kitchen.
Your hands are your resume.

11:12.697 --> 11:14.765
Here, look at this.

11:14.799 --> 11:16.467
See this? This is where

11:16.501 --> 11:17.468
the knife handle hits.

11:17.502 --> 11:18.769
It took me years to get this.

11:18.803 --> 11:20.504
And that guy

11:20.538 --> 11:22.539
is from a tray
of hot beef bones

11:22.574 --> 11:25.375
when somebody ran into me.

11:25.410 --> 11:27.277
I got this cutting tomatoes.

11:27.312 --> 11:29.513
Oh. Well, that's a good start.

11:31.416 --> 11:32.349
And what about these?

11:36.354 --> 11:38.322
From basketball.

11:38.356 --> 11:40.090
Not really kitchen-related.

11:40.125 --> 11:41.225
Hmm.

11:58.743 --> 11:59.843
Where's your bathroom?

12:01.613 --> 12:03.614
- Uh, it's up the stairs.
- Okay, great. Yeah.

12:04.716 --> 12:05.682
You all right?

12:08.953 --> 12:10.721
<i>Ugh.</i>

12:10.755 --> 12:13.657
Bad grasshoppers.
I'm just gonna get you some...

12:13.691 --> 12:14.658
you can't hear me.

12:21.666 --> 12:23.233
Hi.

12:23.268 --> 12:25.435
Sorry. Uh, uh...

12:25.470 --> 12:27.304
sunglasses.

12:27.338 --> 12:29.406
Oh, God. I was supposed to
put them in the mailbox.

12:29.440 --> 12:32.309
I'm sorry. C-come in.
I'll see if they're upstairs.

12:36.514 --> 12:38.148
She can't hear that.

13:23.934 --> 13:25.935
Don't take this the wrong way,

13:25.970 --> 13:28.238
but you look the way I feel

13:28.272 --> 13:29.973
about this whole trial thing.

13:31.041 --> 13:32.141
Oh, God.

13:32.176 --> 13:33.877
That starts tomorrow,
doesn't it?

13:35.012 --> 13:37.113
Are you okay? What's going on?

13:38.148 --> 13:39.682
I almost

13:39.717 --> 13:42.785
slept with chef Jeff
last night.

13:42.820 --> 13:47.624
I'm sorry. The guy that
Melody was sleeping with?

13:47.658 --> 13:49.592
- You almost...
- Never mind.

13:49.627 --> 13:52.462
No, I'm sorry. I don't
mean to sound all judge-y.

13:52.496 --> 13:54.564
What happened?

13:54.598 --> 13:56.499
Nothing.

13:56.534 --> 13:59.335
Well, we ate these
fried grasshoppers...

13:59.370 --> 14:01.304
and...

14:01.338 --> 14:03.273
Okay, now you're
making stuff up.

14:04.475 --> 14:07.210
Wow, you did have
a weird night.

14:07.244 --> 14:08.311
Anyway,

14:08.345 --> 14:10.480
we didn't...

14:10.514 --> 14:12.348
you know, because

14:12.383 --> 14:14.083
I threw up.

14:14.118 --> 14:16.419
Oh my God. 5 yeah.

14:16.453 --> 14:19.222
So embarrassing.

14:19.256 --> 14:21.958
Hey, I'm sure he understands.

14:21.992 --> 14:23.026
You were nervous.

14:23.060 --> 14:25.061
Everybody is
on their first time.

14:25.095 --> 14:26.963
It wasn't my first time.

14:29.233 --> 14:30.867
Really?!

14:30.901 --> 14:32.902
Why are you so shocked?

14:32.937 --> 14:34.804
You think you're the only
person who's had sex?

14:36.774 --> 14:38.975
Uh... actually,

14:39.009 --> 14:41.711
I, uh, haven't.

14:42.913 --> 14:44.781
You and Emmett...

14:44.815 --> 14:46.816
- never?
- Never.

14:46.850 --> 14:48.918
Wow.

14:48.953 --> 14:49.953
Wow.

14:51.822 --> 14:53.456
- Wow!
- Okay.

14:53.490 --> 14:54.757
That was one more
wow than you needed.

14:54.792 --> 14:56.392
No! I'm sorry.

14:56.427 --> 14:57.794
I just thought that you...

14:57.828 --> 15:00.530
yeah, I know.

15:00.564 --> 15:03.666
I don't exactly give off
the virginal vibe.

15:06.337 --> 15:09.305
Do you think I ruined
everything with Jeff?

15:09.340 --> 15:12.275
Well, as you know,

15:12.309 --> 15:15.345
I'm not exactly an expert
on these things.

15:15.379 --> 15:18.448
But no, I don't think
that you ruined everything.

15:21.151 --> 15:23.186
It really shouldn't be
that painful.

15:23.220 --> 15:26.189
My opening will be short
and to the point.

15:26.223 --> 15:28.191
Just a quick question.

15:28.225 --> 15:30.093
Shouldn't angelo be here
for this?

15:30.127 --> 15:32.128
<i>Angelo's returning</i>
<i>from his job upstate.</i>

15:32.162 --> 15:34.030
He assures me he'll
be present tomorrow.

15:34.064 --> 15:35.999
No. He's back.
I just saw him this morning.

15:37.201 --> 15:40.803
Oh. Oh. Right.

15:40.838 --> 15:41.938
Anyway, after opening,

15:41.972 --> 15:42.972
<i>I'll be calling Colleen</i>
<i>to the stand.</i>

15:43.007 --> 15:44.941
So we're going with
the conspiracy theorist.

15:44.975 --> 15:47.810
She's a lactation consultant with
compelling first-hand testimony.

15:47.845 --> 15:49.679
If she holds up.

15:49.713 --> 15:52.615
Now, the girls will
be front and center, right?

15:52.650 --> 15:54.651
Well, we don't want them
to miss too much school.

15:54.685 --> 15:55.885
<i>They won't have</i>
<i>to be there every day.</i>

15:55.919 --> 15:59.555
When they do show up, they should
obviously be well-dressed.

15:59.590 --> 16:01.791
And tell 'em not to hold
back on the waterworks.

16:01.825 --> 16:03.493
Not to be crass.

16:03.527 --> 16:04.727
Too late.

16:08.599 --> 16:10.600
So I'm thinking, Halloween only
comes once a year, right?

16:10.634 --> 16:14.337
And everybody throws in
50 bucks, maybe even 100 bucks,

16:14.371 --> 16:16.673
we could throw something
amazing with a great band,

16:16.707 --> 16:19.242
smoke machines. It'll be... hey!

16:19.276 --> 16:21.210
Gaby, I'm looking for
somebody to co-host

16:21.245 --> 16:22.478
